10. Span of Agreement and Discontinuance.

Upon the occurrence of any of the events listed below, this agreement may be terminated by either party without incurring any liability or obligation towards the other, except for any fees or payments already due and payable:

a) Material breach of any provision of this agreement by one party that is not cured within 30 days following written notice of such breach;
b) Filing of a petition in bankruptcy by either party, or the appointment of a receiver for either party;
c) Discontinuation of the business of either party for any reason;
d) Any other event that makes it impracticable for either party to carry out its obligations under this agreement.

In the event of termination due to reasons not specified in subparagraphs (a) through (d), either party may be entitled to compensation at the sole discretion of the non-terminating party, and such compensation, if any, shall be determined based on the remaining value of the services provided up to the date of termination.
